original_title: Richmond: Van Duzer Street - Cunard Avenue
text:
Clifton and Grymes Hill, Staten Island: A general view northeastward across the villages of Clifton (right) and Grymes Hill (left), as seen from the hill above Van Duzer Street between Cunard and Wandel Avenues. The thoroughfare running from the center fore- to background is Van Duzer Street. The rectangular 3-story building in the center of the photograph is the Barnaby furniture factory at Targee Street and Waverly Place. On the horizon is the Upper New York Bay.

View 3 shows Grymes Hill. The houses at the foot of the hill are scattered along Hillside Avenue.

October 16, 1926
Views 1, 2, 3

P. L. Sperr
